<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 24 at 7:20PM CST  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Zavala
and Frio Counties through 800 PM CST...
At 720 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Loma Vista, or 15 miles northeast of Big Wells, moving
northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pearsall, North Pearsall, Moore, Derby, Divot, Bigfoot, Bluff,
Schattel, and Three Oaks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
